comments.message:
The problem here is that if we publish this right now, nobody outside of Sierra will be able to download using the GitHub manifest anymore. I'm not sure it would block that many people but still, it's an issue IMHO.
We should transform the 'default' in 'notdefault,proprietary' IMHO, so that it needs to be explicitly declared using -g default,proprietary that you also want to download the proprietary stuff.

commits.commitMessage:
Provide a symlink for releases

This is to maintain compatibility with the documented format.

The manifest has moved from <tag>.xml to <tag>/legato.xml has
to make space for storing other manifests for a particular release.
That's however not the case yet, and the documented format is
still <tag>.xml

Resolves: LE-9971
Change-Id: I1862d4d0f965c7cc787490da16c6329b21e05e4f
commits.subject: Provide a symlink for releases
